						               													<description>Subtitled &amp;quot;The Wild and Windy Game of Survival&amp;quot;.  Hurricane Hugo strikes, and the players move around the board trying to reclaim insurance adjustments, find their lost dog, and so on.  The system is a straightforward roll-and-move system, with certain spaces having set effects and other spaces having you draw from either a deck of harmful cards (which take your money) or a deck of beneficial cards (which give you money).  The one with the most money after everyone reaches the Finish space is the winner.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;From the rules:&amp;#10;&amp;quot;Each player is the proud owner of two homes - one beach house and one primary residence; two cars - a Volvo wagon and a BMW; a black Labrador named 'Stud'; $100,000 in stocks and cash.  Net worth of each individual is $500,000.&amp;quot;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Half of the single rules sheet is a historic description of Hurricane Hugo's devastation.  The game itself is darkly humorous.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
